# Vercel Web Analytics Configuration

## Summary
Fixed and properly configured Vercel Web Analytics for this Vue + Vite project by correcting the placement of the Analytics component in App.vue.

## Changes Made

### Modified Files
- **src/App.vue**: Fixed the Analytics component placement
  - Removed incorrectly placed `<Analytics/>` from the script section
  - Added `<Analytics />` component inside the `<template>` section, as per official Vercel documentation

## Implementation Details

The project already had `@vercel/analytics` v2.0.1 installed in package.json, but the Analytics component was incorrectly placed outside the template tag in App.vue.

Following the official Vercel documentation (https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart), the correct implementation for Vue projects is:
```vue
<script setup>
import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/vue'
</script>

<template>
  <Analytics />
</template>
```

The Analytics component is now properly integrated at the root level of the application (App.vue), which ensures analytics tracking is active across all routes and views.

## Verification Steps Completed

✅ Dependencies installed using pnpm
✅ Build completed successfully with no errors
✅ Linter (ESLint) passed with no errors
✅ No tests to run (none defined in package.json)

## Next Steps

To activate Web Analytics in production:
1. Deploy the application to Vercel
2. Navigate to your Vercel dashboard → Analytics section
3. Click the "Enable" button to activate Web Analytics
4. Analytics data will begin collecting after deployment and user visits

The Analytics component will automatically track page views and send data to Vercel's analytics service once enabled in the dashboard.
